<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[printed]♀ [symbol handwritten] Stephens, 1835 M.Heidemaa des. [printed]&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus junci" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1835 M.Heidemaa det.&quot; [printed]. Condition: legs partly destroyed, left midleg missing, the apical flagellomeres missing, apex of left forewing broken. BMNH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. junci" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="junci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephens, JF" journalOrPublisher="Baldwin and Cradock, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 312" refId="B169" refString="Stephens, JF, 1835. Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata. Baldwin and Cradock, London 7: 1 - 312" title="Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata." volume="7" year="1835">Stephens (1835)</bibRefCitation>
refers to syntypes (&quot;Devonshire and near Windsor&quot;). Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, WF" journalOrPublisher="Trustees of the Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B74" refString="Kirby, WF, 1882. List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae. Trustees of the Museum, London" title="List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae." year="1882">Kirby (1882)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned a &quot;Type of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. junci" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="junci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, this cannot be regarded as a lectotype designation, even though he was apparently only able to locate a single specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus busaei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="busaei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus busaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Snellen van Vollenhoven, 1858. Photos of the lectotype and of the penis valve were checked. Left midleg and two segments of the right antenna missing; the genital capsule is glued on a card. RMNH. This nominal taxon was previously treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. nec Serville, 1823. Haris and later 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacourt, J" journalOrPublisher=")" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="77 - 108" refId="B105" refString="Lacourt, J, 2000. Liste des especes de la famille des Tenthredinidae decrites par J. G. Audinet-Serville, en Mai 1823 et par A. L. M. Le Peletier Comte de Saint-Fargeau, en Aout 1823, avec designation de lectotypes [Hymenoptera, Symphyta]. Revue francaise d'Entomologie (N. S.) 22 (2-3): 77 - 108" title="Liste des especes de la famille des Tenthredinidae decrites par J. G. Audinet-Serville, en Mai 1823 et par A. L. M. Le Peletier Comte de Saint-Fargeau, en Aout 1823, avec designation de lectotypes [Hymenoptera, Symphyta]. Revue francaise d'Entomologie (N. S." volume="22" year="2000">Lacourt (2000)</bibRefCitation>
studied the syntypes (3 ♂) of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Serville, but not their genitalia. Based on their penis valve structure, none of the syntypes fits 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct.: the two syntypes (among them the one labelled as lectotype) represent 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the third one is a male of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Serville is placed here as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by designating its lectotype (see also under 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus junci" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Stephens, 1835) has to be used for 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. nec Serville.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus thargitai" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thargitai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus thargitai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zombori, 1994. The holotype and some paratypes (2♀, 4♂) were studied. HNHM.
</paragraph>
